<subSubSection id="C3776556EEEA3B8EFC9AFCDFFC44FC50" pageId="443" pageNumber="444" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEEA3B8EFC9AFCDFFC44FC50" blockId="443.[810,1452,615,2070]" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEA3B8EFC9AFCDFFC25FCEA" bold="true" box="[863,992,785,811]" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is the combination of Latin words 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEA3B8EFC78FCFDFC16FC8C" box="[957,979,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">bi</emphasis>
(=double) and 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEA3B8EFB4DFCFDFB7EFC8C" box="[1160,1211,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">dens</emphasis>
(=a tooth), referring to the pair of ventrodistal denticles on the surface of the labrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EEEA3B88FC9AFC57FEBBF7D7" lastPageId="445" lastPageNumber="446" pageId="443" pageNumber="444" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEEA3B8EFC9AFC57FB3FFAAC" blockId="443.[810,1452,615,2070]" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEA3B8EFC9AFC57FB9BFC72" bold="true" box="[863,1118,921,947]" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Description of female</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFB7CFC57FAE8FC72" box="[1209,1325,921,947]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294A</figureCitation>
) with stout prosome and elongate urosome; body length 1.48 mm. Prosome 0.93 mm long: cephalosome clearly defined from inflated metasome; first and second pedigerous somites defined, but third and fourth pedigerous somites completely fused forming brood pouch. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFCF7FBABFC60FBBE" box="[818,933,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294B</figureCitation>
) slender, 5-segmented: genitalsomite 68×294 μm, much wider than long; 4 abdominal somites gradually narrowing, 84×193, 84×123, 82×110, and 68×105 μm, respectively. Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFB76FB05FAE9FB24" box="[1203,1324,1227,1253]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294C</figureCitation>
) gradually narrowing distally, 3.6 times longer than wide (130×36 μm): armed with 6 setae; proximal and dorsal setae located at 32 and 63% of ramus length, respectively; all setae shorter than width of ramus at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEEA3B8EFC9AFAB8FB92F900" blockId="443.[810,1452,615,2070]" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFC1CFABBFB92FA51" box="[985,1111,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294D</figureCitation>
) 64×89 μm, tapering, with rounded and sclerotized distal margin. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFABBFA59FCA2FA15" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294E</figureCitation>
) 170 μmlong, 6-segmented; armatureformula 3, 17, 7+aesthetasc, 3, 2+aesthetasc, and 11+2 aesthetascs; setae naked and relatively short; setae on first segment not enlarged. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFBC2F9D1FBBDF9FB" box="[1031,1144,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294F</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; coxa, basis, and first endopodal segment unarmed; compound distal endopodal segment 3.1 times longer than wide: armed with 5 setae (2 located at base of terminal claw) plus terminal claw, 33 μm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEEA3B88FC9AF907FDDEF835" blockId="443.[810,1452,615,2070]" lastBlockId="445.[136,778,1669,2070]" lastPageId="445" lastPageNumber="446" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFC01F907FBF3F925" box="[964,1078,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig. 294G</figureCitation>
) bearing smooth ventral lobe, pair of ventrodistal denticles near midline, patches of minute setules ventrodistally, and with concave posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEA3B8EFC64F8FEFBD7F88B" box="[929,1042,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 294" captionStartId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure-20@444.[194,1392,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="444" captionText="FIGURE 294. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, ventral; D, rostrum; E, antennule; F, antenna; G, labrum; H, mandible; I, maxillule; J, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D–J, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="443" pageNumber="444">Fig.294H</figureCitation>
)withbroadcoxalgnathobasebearing 5 teeth and 1 distal, spinule-like subsidiary denticle: basis with 1 setaonmedial margin; exopod armedwith 4 setae; setae becoming gradually shorter from proximal to distal; endopod armed with 2 and 5 setae on first and second segments, respectively; middle setaon second endopodal segment markedly longer than other endopodal setae. second exopodal segment with short trace of articulation on outer side. Legs 2–4 with rudimentary inner coxal seta (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEC3B88FF55F907FEE3F925" box="[144,294,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 295" captionStartId="445.[136,245,1533,1559]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,246,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-260@445.[136,1451,221,1499]" captionTargetPageId="445" captionText="FIGURE 295. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: A, E, 0.02 mm; B–D, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591885/files/figure.png" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Fig. 295C, D</figureCitation>
); outer seta on basis also small; all setae on endopod naked; outer setae on exopod small and bluntly tipped. Second endopodal segment of leg 4 elongated, about 4 times longer than first. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEEC3B88FF30F89CFE77F8AD" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[245,434,1874,1900]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Bysone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEC3B88FF30F89CFEC3F8AA" box="[245,262,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEC3B88FED1F89CFE77F8AD" box="[276,434,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">brevicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEEC3B88FE7CF89CFDD6F8AD" bold="true" box="[441,531,1874,1900]" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEEC3B88FE7CF89CFDD6F8AD" box="[441,531,1874,1900]" pageId="445" pageNumber="446" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, except formula IV, I, 4 for second exopodal segment of leg 1. Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEEC3B88FD57F8BAFCC7F84F" box="[658,770,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 295" captionStartId="445.[136,245,1533,1559]" captionTargetBox="[170,1428,246,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-260@445.[136,1451,221,1499]" captionTargetPageId="445" captionText="FIGURE 295. Bysone bidens sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: A, E, 0.02 mm; B–D, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591885/files/figure.png" pageId="445" pageNumber="446">Fig. 295E</figureCitation>
) small, consisting of 1 seta located on slight ventrolateral lobe and lobate tapering exopod, notarticulated at base, armed distally with 2 unequal setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655EEED3B89FF4DF8BDFE04F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591883" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4591883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591883/files/figure.png" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" startId="444.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[240,1350,219,1841]" targetPageId="444">
